data.title: Judge denies Binance's request for arbitration in crypto loss dispute. Customers can pursue claims. US District Judge Andrew Carter rules in Southern District of NY. Binance failed to inform customers about changes to terms.
data.description: A federal judge in the Southern District of New York rejected a request for arbitration from cryptocurrency exchange Binance (CRYPTO: BNB) in a case related to customer claims on losses from unregistered tokens. Judge Andrew Carter stated that Binance did not sufficiently notify its customers about changes to its terms of usage, which included an arbitration mandate and a class-action waiver. Customers are now permitted to pursue their claims against Binance. This ruling follows a dispute over the alleged class-action waiver within Binance’s terms. The full story can be found on Benzinga.com.

data.title: Federal Reserve challenges subpoenas in Jerome Powell investigation privately. Legal battle ongoing with undisclosed grounds, tensions with Trump admin.
data.description: The Federal Reserve is contesting two subpoenas issued in a criminal investigation by U.S. Attorney Jeanine Pirro involving Chair Jerome Powell. The Fed is pushing for the dismissal of the subpoenas in sealed proceedings, potentially relieving it from the need to respond, according to a report by The Wall Street Journal. The specific legal grounds being asserted by the Fed have not been disclosed. Typically, in high-profile cases, parties challenge subpoenas as excessively broad or seeking protected information. This legal showdown is happening in private due to secrecy rules governing criminal investigations before a grand jury. No immediate response was provided by the Federal Reserve to Benzinga's request for comment. This development is occurring amidst mounting tensions between the Federal Reserve and the Trump administration. Jerome Powell disclosed in January that... data.title: Global governance seminar in Geneva marks launch of English edition of "China's Governance Under Xi Jinping's Leadership."
data.description: On February 27, 2026, in Geneva, a seminar focusing on global governance took place at the Palais des Nations. The event also marked the introduction of the English version of the initial volume of "China's Governance Under Xi Jinping's Leadership." This development was reported by Xinhua News Agency. The seminar brought together a diverse audience to discuss these topics, further highlighting their importance. Director-General of the event emphasized the significance of such discussions and the publication, underscoring the impact they can have on global dialogue and understanding. The event showcased the commitment to sharing insights on governance practices and promoting dialogue among various nations. It served as a platform for exchanging ideas and perspectives on governance approaches, fostering a collaborative environment for addressing global challenges effectively.
